--------------------------------
Modified version by VRoyer 25/07/08
--------------------------------
rule and compass construction +  written justification

* German version created

* As wims does not exist in german, variable taal cannot be wims variable lang

 Major  change in exercise processing:
-----------------------------------
  ** only one exercise in a serie  (tasks=1)
  ** two steps  (counter=1 or 2)
  ** step 1 is geogebra construction
  ** step 2 gives a textarea form to type in the construction protocol
    no checking on the text !! just to store the student description
  ** $precision : !item precision of 0.1,0.25,1 (cf intro and var.init) instead of 0.5,1,1.5

* Major changes in  $type (algo. from ggb to wims, for getting the elements of applet)
 ---------------------------
   ** get all ggb object of names in $ALPHABET,$alphabet
   ** encode points by point@A@x@y   that is take the names
   ** from wims to applet : 
      only points whose names are required (in $ptnames) are reconstructed
      that could be changed very simply ...(take names in $ALPHABET)

* Increased feedback ; reconstruct applet as modified by user:
----------------------
  ** a specific error message when there is not enough / too much constructed points
     -> then gobakc=1 and applet given back
  ** when user does not build circles / lines as requested, then error message and goback=1
     -> applet is given back
  ** when goback, the user points are drawn in red ; the initial points in blue
  ** status done and figur false : the figur is shown back for error analysis

* Changes in printing :
---------------------
  ** titles with yellow background
  ** buttons as well !
  ** var $question maybe a list of two items
      first item = the text ; second item = a math formula
        see  titles for Thales  exercises (9, 11)

* Bug corrected in parallelogram exercises (with circles, ex. 7) :
------------------------------------------------------- 
   ** distance tests were insufficient in ex. with circles
    -> did not exclude crossed parallelograms
    -> testing  now  the equality of two vectors*** 

Bug corrected in kyte exercises (ex 4) :
------------------------------------------------------- 
   ** only one case was tested
    -> two kites whether [AC] or [BD] is the symmetry axis
    -> testing  now  othogonality of diagonals (sacalr product null)
       plus that one triangle is isosceles
